channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Hey, It's Worked So Far! Kamala Harris to Mark 2nd Anniversary of Dobbs With More Fearmongering
Biden's latest border order may embolden migrants to flout immigration laws, commit marriage fraud
item.description: Former immigration agency officials and experts spoke to reporters this week ahead of an expected parole-in-place executive order from President Biden.

item.title: Romney on GOP Meeting: I Went to Listen to Trump, Not Support Him
item.description: Sen. Mitt Romney, R-Utah, told a reporter Wednesday that he attended last week's meeting with Republicans not to support former President Donald Trump but to hear what his plans for the country would be, should he win the November election.

item.title: Marlon Wayans' Cringeworthy Interview With Nathan Wade About His Relationship With Fani Willis
White House 'cheap fakes' response to Biden videos part of push for social media censorship: expert
item.description: The White House is defending President Biden against "cheap fake" videos amid "election buzzword" tactics, dismissing critics as threatened by fact-checkers.

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: SEC Latest Deep State Agency to Protect Bidens
item.description: The SEC allegedly avoided charging Hunter Biden as part of a scheme to defraud a Native American tribe because his father, Joe Biden, was vice president at the time, and that's more evidence of how far the deep state has gone to protect the Bidens, Rep. James Comer said.

item.title: Leftist NYT Scribe Nicholas Kristof Weakly Admits Progressive Policies Are Destroying West Coast Cities
‘Life and death’: House GOP faces mounting pressure to target DEI in medical schools
item.description: More than 50 conservative groups are pushing Speaker Mike Johnson to take up a bill to roll back diversity, equity and inclusion efforts at medical schools.

item.title: Hung Cao to Newsmax: Republicans Can Win Va. Senate Race
item.description: Virginia Republican Senate candidate Hung Cao, citing recent successes by GOP candidates in the state, expressed optimism Wednesday on Newsmax about his chances in November's election against Democrat incumbent Sen. Tim Kaine.

item.title: Jim Banks Wants to Know Why Merrick Garland Refuses to Prosecute Death Threats Against His Family
Biden campaign manager dodges question on whether immigration executive order will get president more votes
item.description: President Biden’s campaign manager on Wednesday dodged questions on whether the president’s executive order giving illegal immigrants a pathway to citizenship was a political move.

item.title: Bill Spadea to Newsmax: If I Win, N.J. Won't Be Sanctuary State
item.description: Bill Spadea, a well-known radio host who this week announced his Republican candidacy for governor of New Jersey, told Newsmax on Wednesday that if elected he would declare on Day One that New Jersey is no longer a sanctuary state.

item.title: Former Obama Mega Fundraiser Now Backs Trump; Biden 'Has Been Asleep at the Wheel'
Senate stumped over COVID origins: What we know – and don’t know
item.description: Many questions remain about the origins of COVID-19, with some theorizing the virus came from a Chinese lab while others suspect the virus emerged naturally from a Wuhan wet market.

item.title: Sen. Hagerty to Newsmax: Biden's Immigration Policies Will 'Backfire'
item.description: Sen. Bill Hagerty, R-Tenn., told Newsmax on Wednesday that President Joe Biden’s attempt at "appeasing Latino voters" is "going to backfire."
